<a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Hagiga 13b</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Emmanuel Vitalis Scherb, a German-speaking poet and critic from Basel, Switzerland, befriended by Longfellow.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">This would be <a href=\"https://archive.org/stream/kritischegeschi01corrgoog#page/n404/mode/2up\"><em>Kritische Geschichte des Chiliasmus</em></a> (1781, p. 336) by Heinrich Corrodi (1752-1793), professor of ethics at the Gymnasium in Zurich. (Many thanks to <a href=\"http://onthemainline.blogspot.com\">Mississippi Fred Macdowell</a> for helping me to locate the exact page in the <em>Chiliasmus</em> with the source.) Max Cavitch in &#8220;<a href=\"http://books.google.com/books?id=rWCqWzR-qKIC\">Emma Lazarus and the Golem of Liberty</a>&#8221; in <em>The Traffic in Poems: Nineteenth-Century Poetry and Transatlantic Exchange</em>, (ed. Meredith L. McGill, 2008), provides some fascinating context concerning Longfellow and his understanding of Jewish myth, history, and peoplehood.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">amended translation and notes by Rabbi Dr. Harry Mordechai Freedman (1901-1982) (from the Soncino Talmud)</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Ezekiel 1:15</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Perhaps from Grk. ** == cobrother. Sandalphon is described as brother of Metatron; v. J.E. vol. XI, pp. 39-40.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">I.e., offers up the prayers of the righteous.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >8</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Ezekiel 3:12.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >9</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">I.e., the vagueness of the expression ‘from His place’ indicates that God&#8217;s place is unknown even to His angels.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >10</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">More on Sandalphon can be learned from Arthur Green&#8217;s <a href=\"http://books.google.com/books?id=J0B-QgAACAAJ&#038;dq=inauthor:%22Arthur+Green%22&#038;hl=en&#038;sa=X&#038;ei=CvevUc7GO5fG4APezoDgCA&#038;ved=0CEsQ6AEwBzgU\">Keter: The Crown of God in Early Jewish Mysticism</a> (1997).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').ani